<seg id=1> Henan Province Holds Economic Cooperation Discussions With Foreign Financial Institutions in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 16, Telegram (Reporter Yu Haisheng). The Henan Provincial Government held economic cooperation discussions here with more than a hundred representatives from 88 foreign financial institutions with offices in Beijing to enhance mutual understanding between the Henan Provincial Government and the international financial world and open up channels of financing for the development of Henan Province. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The vice president of the People's Bank of China, Chen Yuan, said in his congratulatory address at the meeting that the Chinese government has already decided to increase the intensity of development in the middle and western regions, is encouraging Chinese and foreign enterprises to invest in the middle and western regions, and has also decided to employ 60 percent or more of foreign bank and government loans in the middle and western regions in the future. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Cauchier, chief representative of the Beijing Representative Office of the Belgian General Bank and chairman of the Beijing Foreign Finance Institute, indicated at the meeting that the Beijing Foreign Finance Institute intends to contribute to the economic construction of Henan Province and the development of the middle and western regions of China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Li Chengyu, standing assistant governor of Henan Province, introduced the natural resources and state of economic development of the province at the meeting. </seg>
<seg id=6> He stated that Henan Province not only has the hardware required for investment by foreign firms, but also has a preferential policy for encouraging foreign firms to invest and develop technical cooperation in foreign trade that has actually been formulated based on national policy in combination with the province. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The competent agencies of the Henan Provincial Government released [a list of] foreign economic technological cooperation projects of the province at the meeting and held discussions regarding the purpose of cooperation in the related projects with representatives at the meeting. </seg>
</p>
